annotation.TEXT: Why have the clouds all started spitting out 1-ups all of a sudden?!
Nope, nothing special. Well, the goal's right here, so I may as well just finish the level again.
Oh, and I guess I should finish eating these berries as well.
Oh, I guess in all the commotion, I missed a paraBABZAIS YALLEY and a Mega Mole.
What the heck?! Why did Yoshi just run off suddenly? There aren't any enemies around... are there?
Hey, everybody. I'm a stupid moron with an ugly face and a big butt and my butt smells, and I like to kiss my own butt.
Be careful of the boos here. (Like I need to tell you that.)
There's more vines. Let's hope that cape gliding lets me keep Yoshi here! (Maybe I should've taken flight again...)
If anyone knows a way to reach the rest of the stuff beyond the goal, let me know!
Ooh, bonus game. Now, I have to do better than I did last time or my name is mud!
But what I really backtracked for was this Yoshi coin. Can't forget those!
Okay, finally. Man, it probably would've been faster to play the room normally by this point.
Alright, I managed to keep the egg in play this time! This is gonna get fun...
And that's probably how I'm normally supposed to reach that Yoshi coin, but it was easy enough to reach with a running jump from below and to the right.
Oh, by the way, they don't cap at three on screen at once. I think you can have as many as the sprite limit will allow for (which I think is five here).
Sorry, but I don't really know anything about gfx-ripping. You'll have to ask someone else to help you with thome new gfx too. (But I do agree that level deseign is the best thing in a hack!)
There's the tops of goalposts and some seaweed, but I don't know what they're used for. Probably just there for decoration.
Now I need another feather. One moment please...
Oh, man. That was nutters, but I want to go back for something I missed before I forget about it.
Nope, just lots of black and purple bricks. Okay, let's Start+Select out and come back.
That unlocks the next level, of course, but I still want to check out a few things in the ghost house. For these things, I'll want a feather, so just give me a moment...
Well, that explains why all the enemis (and my flower) are black, and much more dangerouos.
And in this room, we have cyan and red coloring, along with squares of dotted line blocks. Wait, didn't I hit the yellow and green switches? How come those colored blocks aren't filled?
The wings probably aren't all that useful unless you can somehow coax Yoshi into coming in here. What you really want is this odd-looking thing which acts as a balloon!
Aw, man. I was able to reach the Yoshi coin, but how can I hit that message box without ditching Yoshi?
To be continued...

Some blocks have "nothing" (which I think is supposed to be a BABZAIS YALLEY shell, or maybe a Death Eater shell, but I have no way to make them visible right now (The naming vote this time had a tie between "BABZAIS YALLEY" and "Death Eater", so I'm going to alternate between them.)).
Now, the other thing I wanted to check out with the cape is at the end of the level, and fortunately, I know a shortcut through the second room.
Okay, now that I've gotten all that out of my system, let's fly over here and start eating some berries!
Demo count: Pancakes
Now, for starters, Zeldara109 informed me that there are 5 Yoshi coins hidden in the upper-left corner of this room, so I'm here at a time when I haven't already gotten 5+ Yoshi coins previously.
There's the last Yoshi coin.
Die, paraBABZAIS YALLEY!
What do ya mean, "yoshi is to stupid"? But I don't wanna loose yoshi! You're mean!
If you have a cape, you can glide down underneath this rope to reach those wall triangles, but there's nothing of importance down there.
Ooh, nice! I took out a 4321rt35J bullet completely by chance!

Well, srry, but since I have a cape, I don't think I'll be loosing yoshi anytime soon! First, I'll get that paraBABZAIS YALLEY out of the way, hit the triple midpoint, and show you that that ? block contains a flower.

And I still manage to get hit, even though I was taking my time there! I was duck-jumping too, but for some reason, I think the boo ring always treats your hitbox as if you aren't ducking while you're super.

I think that makes 11 Yoshi coins collected in this level so far, but geez, do I really need all these keys? Well, I think I'll wait for the balloon to run out and then carry a key with me, just in case.
GAAAAAMMMEEE!!! Of course, I would just so happen to crash into another boo offscreen...
Alright, now back in the present day and age, let's resume the adventure and explore the "HOUSE IN YALLEY"!
Ooh, a red level! That means it'll have two exits, right? Find out next time! ...Maybe.
Yeah, now it's possible to safely collect these lower Yoshi coin halves down here, which in turn produces more invisible ? blocks with more prizes to reveal!
Ooh, it's green and purple! Those colors are perfect for a scary ghost house! Hey, I see a Yoshi coin!
Man, waiting for boo rings is boring, but I'm not feeling reckless right now.
Oops. I meant to eat that paraDeath Eater. Oh, well. I'll eat the next one.
Okay, now over here, you can collect the upper Yoshi coin halves, and that'll cause invisible ? blocks to appear beneath them. Hit those blocks to get various items!
I'd better hustle. I don't really have time to waste fooling around with paraBABZAIS YALLEYs.

And sure enough, there were indeed 5 Yoshi coins hidden up there! How I never found those before, I don't know, but that means, with or without the Yoshi wings, it's possible to collect 8 Yoshi coins in this level! (If you're going to use the wings, only collect a total of 4 Yoshi coins beforehand.)
Oh, by the way, the 4321rt35J bullets are slide-killable, but if you have Yoshi, he may try to flee anyway, so be ready to catch him quick! (Or, just dismount him before doing the slide-killing.)
Oh, yeah. Also, eeries. Be careful of them too. (Well, duh.)
Over here, we have a ton of tall goalposts, and a gap in the left wall.
Oh, god. And now I'm going to be creating more clouds. This is gonna get ridiculous!
I'm guessing those dotted blocks were inserted as Map16 tiles, so they ignore the switch palace statuses.
Whoa. I somehow ended up suddenly holding this Death Eater shell. I'd do a shell jump, but it's totally unnecessary to reach everything here.
Thanks for the boost, paraDeath Eater!
What, are those two boos like lined up perfectly vertically or something? At least I still have my feather, just like I planned.

If you want, you can take out another 4321rt35J bullet here with a shell. Just note that you can't kill them by stomping on them. The 4321rt35J model has the same stomp resistance as a giant green bubble.
Sounds ovely.
Nice clock. You know what would be interesting, if someone could get the hands on the clock to move in real time, maybe reading off of the in-game timer or perhaps the computer's clock!
Yeah, perfect! I get to keep my current name!
These are where I'm guessing the checkpoint 1-up spots are here.
Now, if I fly beyond the right wall of this area, will I find anything special?
Didn't I miss a bunch of coins? Or maybe they all start doing that when I've collected ten coins from them in total.
Um, that's weird. This small section of stairs right here has a bit of an oddity, but the stairs still function like a slope as normal, so don't worry.
You know what, I'm just gonna commit suicide right now and come back with another Yoshi.
There's another "balloon", and a key. I don't think there are any keyholes in this place, but if there is one that I'm unaware of, let me know!
Now, let's get killed in a silly way before returning to the present time.
Okay, we're all set and ready to go.
Hello, and welcome back to me going back in time to revisit a level again! This time, to show off a couple things I did not know about!
Also, moons.
Assuming of course, that I can get in it...
Not that I'm aware of. How about that tiny gap in the left wall?
Hey there, Mega Mole. Want to become part of my meal? That's fine with me!
BURN! BURN TO THE GROUND! BURN! WOO! WOO! BURN TO THE GROUND! BURN TO THE GROUND! BURN! BURN! TRI-FORMATION!
Something's not right here...
Oh, but don't go for those Yoshi coin halves down there right now, or it won't end well for you. Don't worry though. We'll be coming back for them soon enough. (That's not soon enough!)
D'oh! And then I screw up and loose my to stupid yoshi to the very 4321rt35J bullet that was meant to preserve him...
And over here, we have an actual goal, with stuff to the right of it.
Whoa. Nice eerie dodge there.
Nuts. I've missed coins from every cloud already. Oh, well. Also, there's ground underneath this row of coins.
Okay, this time, I'm not going to let that happen. I'm going to switch to my flower just in case the game pulls that stunt again, just to make sure I'll keep my feather.
Well, I guess the key was useless after all...
And we have miscellaneous spinning turn blocks added to the decor as well.
Why do I keep letting Yoshi poop into a pit?
Now, if you spin jump off of a boo and ride it upwards, you can land on an upper ledge and pretty much skip this whole room!
Alright, time for the next level, "BlACK HEAT BAT GUYS". (I think that's a lower-case "L" in the first word there.)
There's a bunch of coins scattered about here, and you can collect them all by carefully bouncing off the ghosts.
Oh, perfect! A 4321rt35J bullet is just what I needed! Now I should be able to hit that message box no problem!
And because of that jerk, I get to miss out on a huge berry feast!
Bonus points if you get that reference. But, yeah. I have no good excuses for that moronic death.
Demo count: 21
More green and purple, with a little bit of orange...
Okay, now for that hammer jerk, I'm going to take my black (?) flower and burn him!
Now, there's a bunch midpoints right in front of the goal, which I guess might be helpful if you skipped the triple midpoint earlier, and you somehow die just before reaching the goal!
Careful. Some of these stairways don't quite connect to the platforms. I'm going to have to talk to the architect of this place and ask what he was thinking with this design...
Demo count: 22
And, now it's time to take off! Who's "to stupid" now?
And I guess I hit them all, 'cause there's the 1-up! (Note: It's possible for the 1-up to get stuck in the ceiling when it spawns if you're unlucky.)
I bet I could've easily kept Yoshi through that whole level if I didn't lose my blue one to that hidden hammer jerk. Then, I could've eaten any of the paraDeath Eaters and flown the whole way.
Yeah, that's kind of silly...

Now, most of that stuff isn't reachable as far as I know, but you will collect several coins, along with two Yoshi coin halves (assuming you're big) during your victory march, bring the total number of collectable Yoshi coins in this level up to 13!
Oh, so there's the culprit! There was a hidden hammer brother inside of the middle column there, and that's what caused Yoshi to flee!
Okay, now let's not moronically slide into oblivion here...
So, by looking at the map of the original game's Valley of Bowser 2 in Lunar Magic, I do believe that the checkpoint 1-up is right around here.
Okay, now is there anything special above these tall goalposts?
I also see slide-killable bubbles!
Outta my way, paraDeath Eater! I'm eating here!

Now, the other thing I want to show is over near the right side of this area. I did ask about this, because I was wondering, and Zeldara109 informed me that the second possible checkpoint 1-up location from the original game still exists here!
Wait, what?
Also, Death Eater shells make for good weapons against the "4321rt35J" bullets. (That must be their model number or something.)
Be careful of the paraBABZAIS YALLEYs that like to fly around here.

As for that Chuck, I think it was meant to summon super BABZAIS YALLEYs, but it was placed in the wrong X position, so instead it was waking up all of the Rip Van Fish in the level (all zero of them).
